A: The issue is with this line:
names.add(dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator().next().getValue(String.class));

You're creating a new iterator each time you call dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator(). This means that you're always getting the first child of the DataSnapshot, regardless of which iteration of the loop you're on.
Instead, you should use the iterator you're already using in the for loop:
names.add(dataSnapshotSnapshot1.getValue(String.class));

